    "Walker was also responsible for the planning of the gallery's east building expansion, designed by architect I M Pei and completed in 1978.": [],
    "In 1961, Walker took as his personal assistant the 25-year-old <a href=\"/brownjc\">J.": [],
    "Carter Brown</a>, whose father, John Nicholas Brown (1900-1979), had been a fellow student with Walker's in Sachs' classes.": [],
    "Brown succeeded Walker in 1969 as Director and Walker assumed the title Director Emeritus.": [],
    "Walker and his wife settled in Sussex, in Amberley (near Arundel), England, and Fishers Island, New York, spending winters in Florida.": [
